. Challenging current political and social policy approaches, this rigorous text discusses innovative solutions to contemporary challenges in a complex care system.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aOlder peoplexCare. 0aOlder peoplexHealth and hygiene. 0aOlder peoplexServices for. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gerontology.2bisacsh1 aCalasanti, Toni, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhillipson, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScharf, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311119675640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447348726423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447348726/original  a978-3-11-119675-6  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles